:R-HSA-174048  a            obo:GO_0031145 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "The degradation of cyclin B1, which appears to occur at the mitotic spindle, is delayed until the metaphase /anaphase transition by the spindle assembly checkpoint and is required in order for sister chromatids to separate (Geley et al. 2001;Hagting et al, 2002)." ;
